Alternatively, this is why Java needs a real namespace mechanism. &quot;package&quot; doesn&#x27;t cut it. See: namespaces in C# or C++, or alternately modules in ML.<p>One thing I like about DI implemented in a language itself is that is that it negates the need to make factories in all cases. So, essentially, imagine if Java had C# style namespace and this was done using Guice-style DI.<p><pre><code>  bind(Persistance::Manager.class).toProvider( 
    new Provider<>() {    
      public Persistance::Manager get() {
        new Persistence::Manager::TransactionAware();
      }
  });</code></pre>
